Merrill Lynch and Co Inc is offeringin the domestic debt market 75 mln dlrs of New Zealanddollar-denominated notes due 1988, said sole manager MerrillLynch Capital Markets.    The notes were assigned a 20 pct coupon and priced at parto yield 150 basis points below comparable New Zealand rates.    Non-callable for life, the issue is rated A-1 by Moody'sand AA by Standard and Poor's Corp. The notes have an annualinterest coupon instead of paying interest semi-annually,Merrill said. Reuter&#3;